markdown: 36 <::A scatter plot with two data series, DDT and Dieldrin, showing Storage (PPM) versus Dosage (MG/MAN/DAY). The x-axis, labeled "DOSAGE (MG / MAN / DAY)", ranges from 0 to 35. The y-axis, labeled "STORAGE (PPM)", ranges from 0 to 300. The plot shows an increasing trend for both series. There is an inset graph in the upper left corner, which appears to be a zoomed-in view of the lower left portion of the main graph, with its own x-axis ranging from 0 to 0.40 and y-axis ranging from 0 to 8. The legend indicates: LEGEND option DDT: [ ] (represented by open circles) option DIELDRIN: [ ] (represented by filled circles) Figure 2::> Storage of DDT (upper line, open circles) and dieldrin (lower line, solid points) in the body fat of people in relation to dosage. Source: https://www.industrydocuments.ucsf.edu/docs/skgh0228
